WEBVTT

00:08.455 --> 00:11.457
"O villain,

00:11.458 --> 00:15.682
"villain,
smiling damned villain,

00:15.848 --> 00:20.937
that one may smile and smile
and be a villain."

00:21.103 --> 00:23.469
No smile...

00:23.470 --> 00:25.192
On such
a beautiful morning.

00:25.358 --> 00:27.923
Shame.

00:32.679 --> 00:34.952
Drink this.

00:35.118 --> 00:38.517
I won't have you dying
before I kill you.

00:45.294 --> 00:46.964
That's it.

00:47.130 --> 00:49.091
Don't be afraid.

00:49.257 --> 00:50.946
[ Laughs ]

00:50.947 --> 00:52.344
[ Spits ]

00:52.510 --> 00:54.199
[ Scoffs ]

00:54.200 --> 00:55.567
You think I'm afraid?

00:57.431 --> 01:00.072
I'm not afraid of you.

01:00.073 --> 01:02.024
You can threaten me
all you want.

01:02.025 --> 01:04.397
You can talk in
your stupid riddles all day.

01:04.563 --> 01:07.317
You can take my world...

01:07.483 --> 01:09.465
You can take my life,

01:09.466 --> 01:12.017
but you won't get my fear.

01:12.018 --> 01:13.786
I'm not afraid of you.

01:13.787 --> 01:15.617
And I'm not going to be.

01:15.783 --> 01:18.474
[ Plastic creaking ]

01:20.872 --> 01:22.478
[ Bottle thuds ]

01:22.479 --> 01:25.114
Ahh.

01:25.115 --> 01:27.879
You think your woman
is afraid?

01:28.068 --> 01:31.925
"He hath given
his empire up

01:32.091 --> 01:35.595
to a whore."

01:35.761 --> 01:37.597
You touch her,
and I'll kill you.

01:37.763 --> 01:41.080
[ Chuckles ]

01:41.081 --> 01:42.352
You understand me?

01:42.518 --> 01:43.716
Are you listening?

01:43.717 --> 01:45.000
You touch my wife,

01:45.001 --> 01:46.690
and I'll kill you!

01:46.856 --> 01:48.303
Get it off of me!

01:48.304 --> 01:49.985
I'll kill you!
Hey!

01:50.151 --> 01:51.840
[ Grunting ]

01:51.841 --> 01:53.726
♪ all is

01:53.727 --> 01:58.480
♪ forgiven

01:58.481 --> 02:01.650
♪ listen

02:01.651 --> 02:06.668
♪ come on, listen

02:06.834 --> 02:09.491
dad's not coming home,
is he?

02:12.495 --> 02:14.009
Don't say that.

02:14.175 --> 02:15.469
It's true, isn't it?

02:15.648 --> 02:16.999
No, it's <i>not</i> true.

02:18.387 --> 02:20.202
Your fa...
[ Doorbell rings ]

02:20.203 --> 02:22.421
[ Sighs ]

02:22.422 --> 02:23.672
I'll be right back,
okay?

02:23.673 --> 02:28.961
♪ Oh, Joey,
I'm not angry any more ♪

02:28.962 --> 02:30.179
[ sighs ]

02:32.015 --> 02:33.182
Mrs. Scott.
Yeah.

02:33.183 --> 02:34.362
Do you remember me?

02:34.528 --> 02:36.773
- Officer Stevens.
- Yeah, I remember.

02:36.774 --> 02:38.408
I know there are detectives
handling things,

02:38.574 --> 02:41.106
but I've been going over
the evidence

02:41.107 --> 02:43.392
and following a few leads
of my own.

02:43.393 --> 02:44.498
Quietly.

02:44.664 --> 02:46.917
Why quietly?
What does that mean?

02:47.083 --> 02:50.315
It means I'm not a Detective,
and this isn't my case.

02:50.316 --> 02:51.797
I-I shouldn't
even be here.

02:51.963 --> 02:53.924
So why <i>are</i> you here?

02:54.090 --> 02:56.672
I became a cop to help people,
Mrs. Scott,

02:56.673 --> 02:59.541
and ever since this case
became official,

02:59.542 --> 03:01.577
I've carried around
the fact

03:01.578 --> 03:03.934
that I sent you away
that first night.

03:04.100 --> 03:06.144
I'm sorry.
I need to fix that.

03:06.310 --> 03:08.917
Okay.
Um, how can I help you?

03:08.918 --> 03:09.981
Quietly?

03:10.147 --> 03:11.369
Okay, um...

03:11.370 --> 03:13.639
Is there anything
that you haven't told us?

03:13.640 --> 03:14.778
Or shown us?

03:16.375 --> 03:18.698
Yeah.

03:18.864 --> 03:20.492
Yeah, just a second.

03:22.535 --> 03:26.331
Nathan brought this back
for our daughter.

03:26.497 --> 03:28.821
And I found it
at the airport, so...

03:28.822 --> 03:30.272
Okay.

03:30.273 --> 03:32.074
You were smart to bag it.

03:32.075 --> 03:35.215
I didn't bag it
because I was [Chuckles]

03:35.381 --> 03:39.531
I just wanted to keep it
the way that it was.

03:39.532 --> 03:41.721
I'd like to have it back
when you're done, please.

03:41.887 --> 03:43.085
Of course.

03:43.086 --> 03:44.703
Anything else?

03:44.704 --> 03:47.602
Anything or anyone suspicious
or out of the ordinary?

03:47.768 --> 03:50.230
You mean besides
his father, Dan?

03:50.396 --> 03:53.942
I know we released him,
but... What do you think?

03:54.130 --> 03:58.634
I don't know.
I've given up on Dan Scott.

04:00.000 --> 04:06.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

04:21.908 --> 04:23.388
Nathan:
Game-winning double.

04:23.554 --> 04:24.890
Baseball.

04:25.056 --> 04:26.641
He loves it.

04:34.721 --> 04:37.360
I thought you said you lost
everything in the fire.

04:39.175 --> 04:41.393
Where are you, son?

04:54.085 --> 04:55.741
Hi.

04:55.742 --> 04:56.942
Hey.

04:56.943 --> 04:59.049
You okay?

04:59.215 --> 05:01.280
He's up for parole.

05:01.281 --> 05:02.552
Xavier.

05:02.718 --> 05:05.951
What?

05:05.952 --> 05:08.600
How can that be?
He murdered Quentin.

05:08.788 --> 05:11.156
They never convicted him
of Quentin's murder.

05:11.157 --> 05:13.542
They convicted him of kidnapping
and aggravated assault,

05:13.543 --> 05:15.594
and now he's up
for parole.

05:15.595 --> 05:17.262
That guy's
a psychotic maniac.

05:17.263 --> 05:18.997
Whether they convicted him
or not,

05:18.998 --> 05:20.237
he needs to be locked up.

05:21.517 --> 05:25.158
He wants to meet with me
before his hearing.

05:25.338 --> 05:26.868
No way.

05:29.192 --> 05:30.872
I think I should.

05:31.038 --> 05:32.578
Why?

05:32.579 --> 05:34.646
I want to look
in his eyes

05:34.647 --> 05:37.420
and see if he's still the same
person he used to be.

05:37.600 --> 05:41.967
♪ ...All full of light

05:42.133 --> 05:44.323
all right, Clay,
talk to me about the person

05:44.324 --> 05:46.658
that you have become.

05:46.659 --> 05:49.578
Well, for instance,
what's your daily routine?

05:49.579 --> 05:51.997
What's a day
in your life like?

05:51.998 --> 05:54.349
I don't know.
Um...

05:54.350 --> 05:55.772
I work a lot.

05:55.938 --> 05:57.603
I spend time with Quinn.

05:57.604 --> 05:59.988
You know, we cook,
play video games,

05:59.989 --> 06:01.695
go to
the comic-book store.

06:01.861 --> 06:03.321
Who do you like?

06:03.509 --> 06:04.572
Wolverine and Batman.

06:04.738 --> 06:06.449
Ah, loners.

06:06.615 --> 06:08.451
Solitary heroes.

06:08.617 --> 06:10.098
Fair enough.

06:10.099 --> 06:11.683
What else?

06:11.684 --> 06:12.956
Well...

06:13.186 --> 06:15.821
I'm awesome in bed,
so she begs me to have sex.

06:15.822 --> 06:16.876
A lot.

06:17.042 --> 06:19.879
Uh...

06:20.045 --> 06:21.610
I don't know.
I mean, I don't know.

06:21.611 --> 06:23.829
We hang out.
We get drunk.

06:23.830 --> 06:26.064
We watch Haley
and Nathan's kids...

06:26.065 --> 06:27.178
not when we're drunk.

06:27.467 --> 06:29.431
She buys me
weird clothes online...

06:29.597 --> 06:31.736
And calls me Sergio.

06:31.737 --> 06:34.144
Geez, no wonder
I'm in here, right?

06:34.567 --> 06:37.188
I'm sad to say you sound
boringly normal.

06:37.354 --> 06:38.314
[ Chuckles ]

06:38.594 --> 06:41.096
I understand your friend Nathan
is missing.

06:41.097 --> 06:42.152
I'm sorry.

06:42.318 --> 06:45.217
How's his family doing?

06:45.218 --> 06:47.552
I think they're holding
their breath.

06:47.553 --> 06:48.603
We all are.

06:52.328 --> 06:56.374
I was, uh, supposed to be
the one to go to Europe.

06:56.596 --> 06:59.169
Why didn't you go?

06:59.399 --> 07:03.402
Because I started having
these stupid fugue episodes,

07:03.403 --> 07:05.425
and Nate wanted
to help me.

07:05.591 --> 07:08.303
Clay, do you feel responsible
for this?

07:08.541 --> 07:10.013
Why the hell
would you ask me that?

07:10.179 --> 07:11.222
Because I know you.

07:11.494 --> 07:13.128
Hell, yes,
I feel responsible.

07:13.129 --> 07:14.267
It should have been me.

07:14.433 --> 07:17.228
He sounds like a good guy.

07:17.417 --> 07:19.117
Yeah.
He's more than that.

07:19.118 --> 07:20.552
He's a great guy...

07:20.553 --> 07:23.055
With an amazing wife
and kids.

07:23.056 --> 07:26.154
I would do anything
for that family.

07:35.663 --> 07:36.902
Do you see him yet?

07:36.903 --> 07:38.520
No. You?

07:38.521 --> 07:39.876
Uh...

07:48.998 --> 07:50.615
Yeah.

07:53.472 --> 07:55.003
Uncle Lucas!

07:55.432 --> 07:57.205
♪ Oh-oh-oh-oh oh-oh

07:57.206 --> 07:59.925
♪ bring 'em all back to life

08:00.437 --> 08:01.676
♪ oh-oh-oh-oh oh-oh

08:01.677 --> 08:04.012
♪ bring 'em all back to life

08:04.013 --> 08:05.130
hey, bud.

08:05.131 --> 08:07.015
♪ Oh-oh-oh-oh oh-oh

08:07.016 --> 08:09.280
♪ bring 'em all back to life

08:09.602 --> 08:12.170
give me a second.
♪ oh-oh-oh-oh oh-oh

08:12.171 --> 08:14.306
♪ bring 'em all back to life

08:14.307 --> 08:16.079
you don't write.
You don't call.

08:16.245 --> 08:18.998
Hi.

08:19.164 --> 08:21.730
♪ Oh-oh-oh-oh oh-oh

08:21.731 --> 08:23.014
[ voice breaking ] Hi.

08:23.015 --> 08:24.616
♪ Bring 'em all back to life

08:24.617 --> 08:27.319
♪ oh-oh-oh-oh oh-oh

08:27.320 --> 08:29.621
♪ bring 'em all back to life

08:29.622 --> 08:32.157
♪ oh-oh-oh-oh oh-oh

08:32.158 --> 08:34.793
♪ bring 'em all back to life

08:38.256 --> 08:40.342
buddy, come here.

08:40.342 --> 08:42.397
Let me get a look at you.

08:42.563 --> 08:44.107
Uh-huh.

08:44.273 --> 08:47.318
Well, you look...

08:47.484 --> 08:48.862
Exactly the same.

08:49.028 --> 08:50.196
I do not!

08:50.362 --> 08:52.137
[ Chuckling ]
I'm serious.

08:52.138 --> 08:55.324
I was thinking by now you'd have
a mustache or something.

08:55.325 --> 08:56.953
[ Chuckles ]

08:57.119 --> 08:59.611
See, Lydia?

09:03.166 --> 09:04.499
Lucas:
She has your eyes.

09:04.500 --> 09:06.212
I think
she looks like Jamie.

09:06.378 --> 09:07.797
[ Chuckles ]

09:08.004 --> 09:09.674
You remember
my sister Quinn.

09:09.840 --> 09:11.256
Of course.

09:11.257 --> 09:12.719
It's good to see you.

09:12.885 --> 09:15.180
You too.
How's Sawyer and Peyton?

09:15.346 --> 09:17.179
They're good.

09:17.180 --> 09:18.597
Well, they <i>should</i> be.

09:18.598 --> 09:20.894
They team up on me
and get their way.

09:22.227 --> 09:23.518
[ Sighs ]

09:23.519 --> 09:25.023
I missed you so much, bud.

09:25.189 --> 09:27.108
Me too.

09:27.274 --> 09:28.807
You better have.

09:28.808 --> 09:31.487
Come on.
Let's go get some food.

09:31.653 --> 09:34.230
- Are you gonna take her?
- Jamie: Yeah.

09:40.903 --> 09:43.905
[ Cellphone ringing ]

09:43.906 --> 09:45.690
[ Grunts ]

09:45.691 --> 09:49.378
[ The dimes' "don't you worry"
plays ]

09:49.379 --> 09:52.509
Hello. [ Grunts ]

09:52.675 --> 09:54.082
This is him.

09:57.670 --> 09:59.855
I understand.

09:59.856 --> 10:02.274
Thank you.

10:02.685 --> 10:04.426
♪ Hiding from someone

10:04.427 --> 10:05.647
hey.

10:05.813 --> 10:08.981
♪ Hiding for no one

10:08.982 --> 10:10.526
uh... Wait.

10:10.850 --> 10:11.883
What?
♪ but not from you

10:13.278 --> 10:15.448
- Hey.
- Oh!

10:15.614 --> 10:18.826
- Chase.
- Baby, I gotta go.

10:18.992 --> 10:20.058
No.

10:20.059 --> 10:21.204
No, no, no.

10:21.370 --> 10:23.412
One more pony ride.

10:23.413 --> 10:25.530
No.
You can't afford it.

10:25.531 --> 10:27.627
Besides, you weren't
that good at it anyway.

10:27.793 --> 10:29.668
♪ Don't you worry about me

10:29.669 --> 10:31.631
♪ I'm not falling down

10:31.797 --> 10:34.572
bye, boys.

10:36.093 --> 10:37.575
Bye, pony.

10:40.880 --> 10:43.142
Did she just leave
in her underwear?

10:43.308 --> 10:44.883
She's a stripper.

10:44.884 --> 10:46.551
I think they do that.

10:46.552 --> 10:47.605
Dude!

10:47.771 --> 10:50.605
Awesome damn night!

10:51.150 --> 10:53.152
Not so loud!
Geez.

10:53.318 --> 10:55.154
What's with you, anyway?

10:55.320 --> 10:56.594
[ Sighs ]

10:56.595 --> 10:58.116
I just got called
to active duty.

10:58.282 --> 10:59.431
What?!

10:59.432 --> 11:01.744
You got drafted?
Can they do that?

11:01.910 --> 11:05.540
I'm in the air force,
Chris.

11:05.706 --> 11:07.489
Really?

11:07.490 --> 11:08.918
Why?

11:10.776 --> 11:13.795
♪ But don't you worry about me

11:13.796 --> 11:16.048
did pony just leave me?

11:16.049 --> 11:17.666
[ Laughs ]
♪ don't you worry about me

11:17.667 --> 11:19.801
♪ I'll be all right

11:19.802 --> 11:24.100
awesome... Damn... Night.

11:24.266 --> 11:26.725
[ Laughs ]

11:26.726 --> 11:27.792
[ Sighs ]

11:33.232 --> 11:35.650
I don't think
you should go to see him.

11:35.651 --> 11:37.905
- I have to.
- Why?

11:38.304 --> 11:40.805
I'm not afraid of him.

11:40.806 --> 11:44.370
I'm not <i>gonna</i> be afraid
of him.

11:44.694 --> 11:46.811
Well, then, you can <i>not</i> be
afraid of him from here.

11:46.812 --> 11:49.531
I want to believe
in forgiveness.

11:49.532 --> 11:53.285
I want to believe
that I have that capacity

11:53.286 --> 11:56.966
in my heart
to forgive someone, but...

11:57.132 --> 11:58.774
Some things
are unforgivable.

12:00.760 --> 12:04.162
I can forgive
my part of it...

12:04.163 --> 12:06.181
But not Quentin's.

12:06.182 --> 12:08.895
I have to go there.

12:09.102 --> 12:10.602
I just...

12:10.603 --> 12:12.565
I have to.

12:12.731 --> 12:15.860
Not "I." "We."

12:16.026 --> 12:17.275
You and me.

12:22.949 --> 12:24.744
You and me.

12:38.590 --> 12:39.926
[ Gasps, shrieks ]

12:46.389 --> 12:48.559
[ Laughs ]

12:48.725 --> 12:50.812
Knock it off, <i>budala.</i>

12:50.978 --> 12:53.929
Hey, man.
Check this out.

12:53.930 --> 12:55.108
[ Grunts ]

12:55.274 --> 12:58.236
Come on, man!
What?

12:58.402 --> 13:01.155
Are you Chuck
on "the gossip girl"?

13:01.321 --> 13:03.908
"No" means "no."

13:04.074 --> 13:06.202
What are you doing here?

13:06.368 --> 13:08.246
I just need some speed.

13:08.412 --> 13:12.447
Kids are eating that stuff
like gummy bears, man.

13:25.470 --> 13:28.391
Dr. Alvarez: So it was Nathan
who introduced you to Quinn.

13:28.557 --> 13:29.747
Well, sort of.

13:29.748 --> 13:31.183
He introduced us

13:31.184 --> 13:33.730
and then forbid me
from seeing her.

13:33.919 --> 13:36.816
Why do you think
he forbid you?

13:36.982 --> 13:38.860
Because he was a client,
I guess.

13:39.058 --> 13:41.593
And what about Nathan made you
want to sign him?

13:41.594 --> 13:42.905
You know,
he was struggling.

13:43.071 --> 13:45.430
He'd been through
some rough times,

13:45.431 --> 13:47.577
but he was driven
to rise above it all.

13:47.766 --> 13:49.662
Like you.

13:49.828 --> 13:51.319
Yeah.

13:51.320 --> 13:53.833
A-and he...
he had a family.

13:53.999 --> 13:56.127
Why do you mention that?

13:56.409 --> 13:59.044
Well, because helping him
was helping them.

13:59.045 --> 14:01.997
You know, they were dreaming
his dream with him.

14:01.998 --> 14:03.215
Sometimes <i>for</i> him.

14:03.216 --> 14:07.135
Clay, do you ever resent
that he...

14:07.136 --> 14:08.931
That he had a family?

14:09.138 --> 14:11.767
You're asking some screwed-up
questions today, aren't you, doc?

14:11.933 --> 14:13.975
Wouldn't be
such a terrible thing

14:13.976 --> 14:15.977
to resent someone
who has something

14:15.978 --> 14:17.231
that you could have had.

14:17.463 --> 14:21.966
I have never resented
Nathan's family for a second.

14:21.967 --> 14:24.019
I've been jealous of them.

14:24.020 --> 14:25.820
Sometimes I still am.

14:25.821 --> 14:28.868
But I've grown to be
protective of them.

14:29.034 --> 14:31.704
You ever resent that you
couldn't protect Sara?

14:31.870 --> 14:34.412
Every day.

14:38.710 --> 14:41.119
You know,
it's interesting, Clay...

14:41.120 --> 14:45.457
That, uh, your job involves
protecting people,

14:45.458 --> 14:47.509
and yet,
in your personal life,

14:47.510 --> 14:49.972
you've struggled to do
just that, isn't it?

14:50.138 --> 14:53.715
I'm just an agent, doc.

14:57.002 --> 15:00.272
What if he's dead
and he's not coming back?

15:00.273 --> 15:01.690
He's coming back.

15:01.691 --> 15:02.941
I don't...

15:02.942 --> 15:05.154
Luke, I need to say
the words out loud

15:05.696 --> 15:06.945
and let them shock me

15:06.946 --> 15:09.114
because I have to face
the reality of the situation.

15:09.115 --> 15:10.785
Nathan is missing.

15:10.951 --> 15:14.653
There's a good chance
that he's not coming back.

15:14.654 --> 15:17.124
The chances are better
that he <i>is.</i>

15:17.290 --> 15:19.624
Look, I know you've done
the research same as me.

15:19.625 --> 15:22.213
95% of all missing persons
are located.

15:22.379 --> 15:24.412
And of the ones that aren't,

15:24.413 --> 15:26.548
most abductees are dead
within three hours.

15:26.549 --> 15:28.366
You don't know
that he's been abducted.

15:28.367 --> 15:30.502
Then where is he?
Where is he?

15:30.503 --> 15:31.636
This is Nathan
we're talking about.

15:31.637 --> 15:33.171
He has been through hell
and back,

15:33.172 --> 15:34.306
and he's overcome
all of it.

15:34.307 --> 15:35.423
So what do you
think happened?

15:35.424 --> 15:36.758
You think
he got amnesia

15:36.759 --> 15:39.344
and he's gone and he's got
a new identity somewhere?

15:39.345 --> 15:40.878
Do you think he left me?

15:40.879 --> 15:43.481
No. He's not home
because he <i>can't</i> come home.

15:43.482 --> 15:45.383
I can feel it
in my soul, Luke.

15:45.384 --> 15:47.863
Haley, this is Nathan,

15:48.070 --> 15:49.904
and he <i>will</i> come home.

15:49.905 --> 15:51.701
Now, say <i>that</i> out loud.

15:57.372 --> 16:01.168
He's coming home.

16:01.450 --> 16:05.587
♪ You can't help
but cross my mind ♪

16:08.541 --> 16:11.142
talk to me about the...

16:11.143 --> 16:14.562
Person you became
after Sara's death.

16:14.563 --> 16:16.531
You were coming to see me,

16:16.532 --> 16:18.516
and then you just stopped.

16:18.517 --> 16:19.895
I never asked why.

16:20.061 --> 16:23.555
I just got tired
of talking about it.

