34:04.792 --> 34:07.601
<i>doesn't matter how far I go,
Jamie Scott.</i>

34:07.602 --> 34:09.351
<i>You're always with me.</i>

34:09.353 --> 34:13.223
<i>Even when I'm in some ghetto
in wherever I'm at.</i>

34:13.224 --> 34:16.059
<i>But, uh, you be good, okay?</i>

34:16.060 --> 34:17.994
<i>Be good to your mom and Lydia,
help out around the house.</i>

34:17.995 --> 34:19.516
<i>I'll be home soon.</i>

34:19.681 --> 34:21.081
<i>You're a good man, son.</i>

34:21.081 --> 34:22.643
<i>I love you.</i>

34:22.810 --> 34:28.327
♪ the rhythm that our hearts
pound out rolls on ♪

34:47.710 --> 34:48.757
Stevens: Psst!

35:05.376 --> 35:07.814
You hurt?
No, I'm okay.

35:07.980 --> 35:10.163
All right,
I'll get you out of here.

35:10.164 --> 35:11.281
Hang on.

35:12.985 --> 35:14.529
There's an exit
through the next room.

35:14.695 --> 35:18.338
If you run into trouble,
shoot first.

35:21.959 --> 35:23.538
Stay near the road.

35:23.704 --> 35:24.961
Look for my squad car.

35:24.962 --> 35:25.979
I'll catch up.
Go.

35:40.361 --> 35:43.057
[ Hoarse voice ]
Welcome back, my friend.

35:43.223 --> 35:44.831
[ Gun clicking ]

35:48.938 --> 35:50.537
[ Laughs ]

35:56.153 --> 35:57.928
[ Pipe clanks ]

36:04.185 --> 36:06.620
Do I have to do
everything myself?

36:12.181 --> 36:15.650
You think I'm a bad person
for what I said?

36:15.651 --> 36:18.687
No, I think you're a great
person for what you said.

36:22.525 --> 36:23.859
I could tell.

36:23.860 --> 36:27.696
When I asked him about Quentin,
I could...

36:27.697 --> 36:30.063
Tell that
he hasn't changed.

36:33.038 --> 36:35.756
The first time
you had to face him,

36:35.757 --> 36:38.092
you were so brave
and strong.

36:38.093 --> 36:40.073
And I fell in love
with you.

36:40.239 --> 36:43.297
And today in that room,

36:43.298 --> 36:45.633
you were just as brave
and strong.

36:45.634 --> 36:47.968
And I fell in love with you
even more.

36:52.757 --> 36:55.809
And I couldn't have done it
without you.

36:55.810 --> 36:57.695
Either time.

37:02.200 --> 37:04.434
You don't think
they'll let him out?

37:06.849 --> 37:12.126
♪ Oh, my God, we are done

37:12.127 --> 37:17.381
♪ so come take my daughter
and come take my son ♪

37:17.382 --> 37:20.367
so, listen,
I know your dad's in town,

37:20.368 --> 37:24.205
but I was wondering
if maybe you wanted to hang out

37:24.206 --> 37:25.456
until I leave.

37:25.457 --> 37:26.703
Just me and you.

37:26.869 --> 37:28.204
And... Maybe Chris.

37:28.370 --> 37:29.956
Okay.

37:30.122 --> 37:31.295
All right.

37:33.333 --> 37:35.086
All right, then.
I'll see you later.

37:35.252 --> 37:37.505
[ Groans painfully ]

37:37.671 --> 37:39.174
Dude...
Dude, you okay?

37:39.340 --> 37:40.675
Yeah, I'm fine.

37:40.841 --> 37:41.968
What's going on there?

37:42.134 --> 37:43.344
Nothing.

37:43.510 --> 37:45.180
Chuck...

37:45.346 --> 37:46.848
I just fell off that stupid bike
you gave me, that's all.

37:47.014 --> 37:49.640
- Let me see.
- No.

37:49.641 --> 37:51.144
Chuck, let me see.

37:51.310 --> 37:54.397
♪... This earth, no, forever

37:54.563 --> 37:56.837
ohh, geez!

37:56.838 --> 37:57.901
Chuck!

37:58.067 --> 37:59.402
Does your...

37:59.568 --> 38:00.991
Does your mom
know about this?

38:00.992 --> 38:02.826
No. And you can't
tell her, okay?

38:02.827 --> 38:04.628
She'll... she'll take
my bike away.

38:06.283 --> 38:07.994
You won't tell her,
right?

38:08.160 --> 38:09.996
How'd you fall?

38:10.162 --> 38:12.519
I don't know. I just...
I hit the curb, and I fell.

38:12.520 --> 38:13.583
It's no big deal.

38:13.749 --> 38:15.339
I gotta go.

38:40.031 --> 38:43.200
♪ If I had a gun

38:43.201 --> 38:46.587
♪ I'd shoot a hole
into the sun ♪

38:46.588 --> 38:51.208
♪ and love would burn
this city down for you ♪

38:51.209 --> 38:52.977
<i>you're a good man, son.</i>

38:52.978 --> 38:54.144
<i>I love you.</i>

38:54.145 --> 38:55.929
♪ If I had the time

38:55.930 --> 38:58.002
right there.
Push in on that.

38:58.168 --> 39:00.046
Hold on.
I can make it better.

39:00.212 --> 39:03.404
♪ And every day would stay
the same with you ♪

39:12.057 --> 39:13.113
what is it?

39:13.114 --> 39:14.811
Does that mean something?

39:14.977 --> 39:16.116
Yeah.

39:16.395 --> 39:17.785
Well, that's good, right?

39:18.063 --> 39:19.253
No.

39:19.254 --> 39:21.734
It's not good at all.

39:22.007 --> 39:24.425
♪ And show you now
what might have been ♪

39:24.426 --> 39:29.513
♪ if all the tears you cry
would fade away ♪

39:29.514 --> 39:30.798
you okay?

39:30.799 --> 39:34.268
♪ I'll be by your side

39:34.269 --> 39:37.688
♪ when they come
to say goodbye ♪

39:37.689 --> 39:41.725
♪ we will live to fight
another day ♪

39:41.726 --> 39:44.298
Dr. Alvarez: Are you worried
about Nathan, Clay?

39:44.464 --> 39:47.981
Am I worried for his safety?
Of course.

39:47.982 --> 39:51.735
But Nathan Scott
is the strongest guy I know.

39:53.056 --> 39:57.270
Wherever he is, however he is,
he's getting stronger.

39:57.436 --> 39:58.775
He'll come home.

39:58.776 --> 40:00.461
And if he can't...

40:00.462 --> 40:03.780
Someone's in for the fight
of their life.

40:03.781 --> 40:05.749
How can you do this?

40:05.750 --> 40:07.280
A cop.

40:09.448 --> 40:12.789
I'm a desk cop.

40:12.790 --> 40:14.458
At least to them, I am.

40:17.479 --> 40:19.167
They're wrong.

40:19.347 --> 40:21.465
They don't want
to make me a Detective?

40:23.212 --> 40:24.485
Fine!

40:29.908 --> 40:33.389
This definitely
pays better.

40:33.555 --> 40:35.641
By the way...

40:35.807 --> 40:38.853
Your wife says hello.

40:39.019 --> 40:40.480
Oof!

40:40.646 --> 40:41.647
Okay. Okay.

40:41.813 --> 40:42.953
Okay.

40:42.954 --> 40:46.152
"Let's be sacrificers
but not butchers.

40:46.324 --> 40:48.988
"Let's kill him boldly
but not wrathfully.

40:49.160 --> 40:52.179
"Let's carve him as a dish
fit for the gods,

40:52.180 --> 40:54.831
not hew him as a carcass
fit for hounds."

40:57.552 --> 41:02.005
"And let our hearts,
as subtle masters do,

41:02.006 --> 41:06.005
stir their servants
to an act of rage."

41:06.171 --> 41:09.313
[ Cellphone rings ]

41:14.369 --> 41:15.569
Good news.

41:15.570 --> 41:19.206
We've reached new
financial agreement.

41:19.207 --> 41:21.492
So, they send
more money...

41:24.078 --> 41:25.900
... and then you die.

41:26.066 --> 41:27.693
♪ If I had a gun

41:27.999 --> 41:31.802
♪ I'd shoot a hole into
the sun ♪ [ Laughs ]

